cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with cognitive radio networks and their energy harvesting schemes. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper involves optimization problems and signal processing techniques. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as machine learning is used to characterize areas of harvesting and spectrum usage. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper proposes an energy efficient approach based on multi-class Support Vector Machine (SVM). 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with RF energy harvesting, which can be related to multimedia signal processing.
